<event name="SHIPYARD_ZOLTAN_FACILITY" unique="true">
	<img planet="PLANET_POPULATED"/>    
	<text>In the distance appears to just be an ordinary planet, though the vast complex built on the surface interests you. Further scans reveal a morbid truth - a primarily automated Auto-ship factory running entirely on Zoltan slave power has been constructed on the surface!</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Approach.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You fly closer to the surface, but are immediately met by a large Auto-Battleship, but it's not attacking yet. "This is Dr. Peron Anderson. Your vessel has been spotted coming concerningly close to the facility. We suggest either stating your business or getting lost."</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_AUTO_ZOLTAN_FACILITY" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Attack the Auto-ship!</text>
				<event>
					<text>The scientist sighs, then ends the call. Weapons spring out of the Auto-ship's hull, and its time for a brawl.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Buy a Zoltan.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"You... want one of our power sources? Well, I guess we don't need THIS many of them, and the scrap is handy... alright, you've got a deal."</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="energy"/>
					<item_modify>
						<item type="scrap" min="-45" max="-65"/>
					</item_modify>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>We'll just leave.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the planet.</text>
		<event>
			<text>You'd have to be insane to tangle with such a massive structure that's undoubtedly of high value to the Rebels.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

