<event name="AUTO_ENGINEER_MISTAKE" unique="true">
	<text>A damaged Engineer vessel orbits this beacon. It appears to still be functional, and a single hull repair drone is patching up some of the damage.</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_ENGINEER_LIFT_DAMAGE" hostile="false"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Hail them.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"Ugh, you aren't here to kill us, are you?" You shake your head. "Oh, good. In that case, maybe you could help us. We had an issue with a prototype Cognitive we were working on. After the Free Roamer incident the Rebellion banned all attempts at creating fully sentient ship AI. We uh... we broke that rule, and it was a terrible mistake. Now the Auto-ship has escaped. You don't suppose you could track it down and destroy it? We can't let command know about this slip-up..."</text>
			<quest event="AUTO_ENGINEER_MISTAKE_QUEST"/>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Pick off the ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>These guys make an easy target. You arm the weapons.</text>
			<ship hostile="true"/> 
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Continue...</text>
				<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Ignore the ship.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Engineer makes no attempt to hail you in return. Just in case, you put a little distance between your ships.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Do something onboard the ship.</text>
				<event load="STORAGE_CHECK"/>
			</choice>
			<choice>
				<text>Do nothing.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
