<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE" unique="true">
	<text>It appears a large generator has been sculpted onto the face of a nearby snow planet. It's quite a spectacle, but something is wrong...</text>
	<preventQuest/>
	<img back="BACK_EVENT_POWERGRID" planet="PLANET_INVISIBLE"/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>A battalion of pirate ships flies away, chased off by a distant Rebel ship. A warning plays over the intercom. "It is recommended that all personnel evacuate Power Grid 800 immediately. Catastrophic reactor failure is imminent. Estimated 3 minutes remaining until collapse."</text>
			<ship load="SHIP_ENGINEER_MOTHERSHIP" hostile="false"/>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>There's time left, swing by and try to salvage some supplies.</text>
				<event>
					<text>As you move in to salvage, you're stopped by a large Engineer vessel. "Damn pirates! We told you to get the hell out of here!" Though the ship moves in to chase you off, you can't help but notice that reactor countdown is still going, and you figure the Engineers must know as well.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Bide the warning and leave.</text>
				<event/>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_ESCAPE">
	<text>Suddenly, the Engineer ship jumps away so abruptly, they must have used an MV drive, leaving you alone with the power core. You receive another warning from the core. "Warning: Reactor instability has reached 99%. Destruction is imminent. Evacuate immediately. Estimated 3 seconds remaining until collapse."</text>
	<instantEscape/>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Crap.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="engines" lvl="4">
		<text>(Upg. Engines) Get the hell out of there.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="engines" lvl="7">
		<text>(Adv. Engines) Get the hell out of there.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE_GOOD"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_DEFEAT">
	<text>You've defeated the Engineer ship, but that victory won't last for long. You receive another warning from the core. "Warning: Reactor instability has reached 99%. Destruction is imminent. Evacuate immediately. Estimated 3 seconds remaining until collapse."</text>
	<hiddenAug>ACH_BOSS_ENGMOTHER</hiddenAug>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Crap.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="engines" lvl="4">
		<text>(Upg. Engines) Get the hell out of there.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE"/>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true" req="engines" lvl="7">
		<text>(Adv. Engines) Get the hell out of there.</text>
		<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE_GOOD"/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_ALMOSTBOOM">
	<text>The Engineer ship has taken critical damage. Before you can get in a finishing shot you're interupted by another alarm. "Warning: Reactor instability has reached 97%. Evacuate the premises immediately. Estimated 1 minute remaining until collapse."</text>
	<hiddenAug>ACH_BOSS_ENGMOTHER</hiddenAug>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Urge the Engineers to stop fighting.</text>
		<event>
			<text>"You think we can just leave? It's a better fate to blow the hell up than face Vance's wrath! I'd rather die fighting the Federation and become a martyr than-" The engineers are cut off by another warning. "Warning: Reactor instability has reached critical levels. Destruction imminent, evacuation mandatory. Time remaining: undetermined. Repeat: reactor-" The message continues to loop, and it seems like it's a good warning. Surely, there's nothing you can do to stop the explosion?</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Send in your crew to fix the reactor, and quickly!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You pull closer to the power core, and drop off your crew. They hurry inside to the control pannel, which is sparking. There's 3 buttons, but their labels are barely legible. Pressing one of them might save the day, but you have no idea which.</text>
					<ship hostile="false"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Press the big red one.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew flips open the protective casing and smashes the button as fast as they can. Now you can only hope it worked...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Press the small blue one.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew flips open the protective casing and smashes the button as fast as they can. Now you can only hope it worked...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Press the square green one.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your crew flips open the protective casing and smashes the button as fast as they can. Now you can only hope it worked...</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="EXTRA_PREP">
						<text>(Emergency Manual) Read the manual.</text>
						<event>
							<text>You rapidly flip through the manual, and sure enough under the section for "Rebel Automated Power Core Explosion Prevention Protocols" it clearly states to press the red button. You relay this to the crew, who flips open the protective casing and smashes the button as fast as they can.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
					<choice hidden="true" req="engineer">
						<text>(Enginer Crew) Have your engineer help.</text>
						<event>
							<text>Your engineer searches deep through their memories and remembers a staff training day where they explained the importance of each button. Recalling the red button was the correct solution, you relay this to the crew who flips open the protective casing and smashes the button as fast as they can.</text>
							<choice hidden="true">
								<text>Continue...</text>
								<event load="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE"/>
							</choice>
						</event>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Leave, now!</text>
				<event>
					<text>You power up the engines and fly as far away as you can, and watch from a distance as the mothership is consumed by a massive explosion that rips through the planet's surface leaving a crater so large you can see it all the way from the other side of the system. You pull a little closer and scrap the wreckage on the outer rim, though the center is leaking heavy radiation and is not safe to journey towards.</text>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Keep fighting to the bitter end.</text>
		<event/>
	</choice>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM">
	<text>An ear splitting explosion reverbs throughout the ship as a deadly inferno consumes the power core. Your ship is caught in the explosion, and takes heavy damage. You fly away as quickly as possible, your engines burning up as you go.</text>
	<damage amount="6" effect="fire" system="engines"/>
	<damage amount="3" effect="fire"/>
	<damage amount="3"/>
	<damage amount="3"/>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE">
	<text>You speed away from the power core as fast as you possible can. You escape the initial explosion, but much of the debris still collides with your ship, causing damage to the hull.</text>
	<damage amount="3"/>
	<damage amount="3"/>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_BIGBOOM_ESCAPE_GOOD">
	<text>Your advanced engines are easily able to get you out in time. You watch the explosion from a safe distance.</text>
</event>
<event name="AUTO_POWERCORE_SAVE">
	<text>A loud beep emminates from the console. "Emergency Reactor Meltdown Prevention button pressed. Stopping countdown to imminent explosion. Reactor stabilized." By some incredible miracle, it appears you've stopped the explosion.</text>
	<choice hidden="true">
		<text>Continue...</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Engineers are amazed. "I-I didn't even know that button was a thing! You've saved all of us... but why? Why put your life on the line just to save a Rebel facility?"</text>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>My moral compass is legendary.</text>
				<event>
					<text>"Perhaps we are fighting for the wrong side here... Regardless, we must leave this facility at once. Vance won't be happy we let that pirate raid almost destroy the reactor and I doubt he'd let us live through it. I'll come with you, and bring everything that I can with me."</text>
					<crewMember amount="1" class="engineer" all_skills="2"/>
					<drone name="COMBAT_ENGINEER"/>
					<autoReward level="HIGH">standard</autoReward>
				</event>
			</choice>
		</event>
	</choice>
</event>

