<event name="JERRY_QUEST" unique="true">
	<text>An MFK Ace ship is conversing with a transport, surprisingly not on an encrypted frequency. You don't have long, but you manage to catch a bit of their conversation. "Yeah, it's crazy. Admiral Vance's got this nephew, Jerome, and the dude's so fond of the guy he was given an ENTIRE sector all to himself. He's made quite the impression on the locals I've heard... never been there myself but I know the co-ordinates. Think I might go there to scout things out myself, out of curiosity."</text>
	<ship load="SHIP_ACE_JERRY" hostile="false"/>
	<choice req="MARKER_BEENTOJERRY" lvl="0" hidden="true" blue="false" max_group="0">
		<text>Continue listening.</text>
		<event>
			<text>The Rebels eventually change conversations to the weather and some conversational politics, but you suspect you might be able to get those coordinates out of them somehow.</text>
			<choice>
				<text>Attack now and force the co-ordinates out of them.</text>
				<event>
					<text>As soon as you attack, the transport jumps away. You prepare to engage the MFK Ace. Be careful - you'll need them to surrender if you want those co-ordinates!</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
					<choice hidden="true">
						<text>Continue...</text>
						<event load="COMBAT_CHECK"/>
					</choice>
				</event>
			</choice>
			<choice hidden="true">
				<text>Politely ask for the co-ordinates.</text>
				<event>
					<text>The Rebel soldiers stare at you, utterly confused. You wait a little longer in desperate hope but, as you should have expected, the Rebels have no intent of giving you the information.</text>
					<ship hostile="true"/>
